  "title": "Production Operations Manager $4K - $5.5K + VB (Hazardous Waste Treatment)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Stable role with established offshore & marine group</li><li>Exposure to hazardous waste treatment technologies</li><li>On-site operational leadership role with decision-making authority</li></ul><p><strong>Role Summary</strong></p><p>Focus on safe, efficient operations involving <strong>evaporation, centrifugation, and filtration systems</strong>, while supporting production planning and commercial decision-making.</p><p><strong>Key Duties</strong></p><ul><li>Manage daily operations of hazardous waste treatment production lines</li><li>Optimise process conditions based on waste characteristics</li><li>Ensure compliance with EHS, SOPs, and regulatory requirements</li><li>Plan production capacity, manpower, and resource allocation</li><li>Oversee equipment reliability, maintenance coordination, and 5S</li><li>Provide technical input to sales on feasibility, capacity, and costs</li><li>Support audits, inspections, and operational documentation</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Chemical, Environmental, Process, or Mechanical Engineering</li><li><strong>Minimum 10 years</strong> of Industrial Plant or Production Line experience</li><li>Background in <strong>hazardous waste treatment, chemical processing, or environmental industries</strong></li><li>Hands-on experience with <strong>evaporation systems, centrifuges, or filtration/solid-liquid separation</strong></li><li>Strong leadership, production planning, and cross-functional communication skills</li><li>Willing to work in a plant-based, on-site operational environment</li></ul><p><strong>Apply Now:</strong> jeffrey@oaktree.com.sg<br /><strong>Contact:</strong> <strong>Jeffrey Chua Kay Hwee</strong><br /><strong>EA License No:</strong> 06C4642 | <strong>EA Reg No:</strong> R1110624</p>",
